<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-209-984  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 209 984.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  March 5 1990 n290 p50(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Undersea fiber cable slated for Asia. (the 7,000 kilometerAsia-Pacific System) (consortium plans fiber optic venture)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Preston, Robert; O'Rorke, Fergus.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A consortium comprised of four international telecommunicationsfirms is planning the construction of ASPAC, the Asia-Pacificfiber optic undersea cable.andP;  The $260 million structure will runfor 7,000 kilometers from Singapore and Tokyo, and will alsofeature spurs to Hong Kong and Shanghai.andP;  ASPAC will provide Chinawith an opportunity to join the international data communicationsnetwork.andP;  The four members of the consortium are Cable andWireless Hong Kong Ltd, Singapore Telecom, Japan's InternationalDigital Communications Inc and the Shanghai Post andTelecommunications Bureau.andP;  US Sprint Communications Co andMercury Communications Ltd are planning members of the group,meaning that they will lease capacity on the cable system upon itscompletion.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cable and Wireless (Hong Kong) Ltd. (communication systems)Singapore Telecom International Private Ltd. (communicationsystems)International Digital Communications Planning Inc. (communicationsystems)US Sprint Communications Co. (planning)Mercury Communications PLC (planning).andO;Topic:     ConsortiaFiber OpticsTelecommunicationsAsiaInternational CommunicationsShanghai. Post and Telecommunictions BureauFacility Construction.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>